ZH: 进行筛检是非常重要的，可以帮助我们发现潜在的健康问题。
EN: Screening is crucial as it helps us identify potential health issues.

ZH: 医生建议每年都要进行筛检，以确保身体健康状况良好。
EN: Doctors recommend getting screened annually to ensure good health.

ZH: 筛检可以让我们及早发现疾病，提高治疗的成功率。
EN: Screening allows us to detect diseases early and improve treatment success rates.

ZH: 这项筛检项目很简单，只需抽一些血就可以了。
EN: This screening test is very simple, just a blood sample is needed.

ZH: 我们应该认真对待筛检的结果，及时进行治疗。
EN: We should take screening results seriously and seek treatment promptly.

ZH: 孕妇应该定期进行筛检，以确保胎儿的健康。
EN: Pregnant women should undergo regular screening to ensure the health of the fetus.

ZH: 口腔筛检是检查口腔健康的有效方法。
EN: Oral screening is an effective way to examine oral health.

ZH: 儿童筛检需根据年龄段来制定具体的计划。
EN: Children's screening plans should be tailored based on their age group.

ZH: 每一个人都应该参加癌症筛检，以及早发现并治疗。
EN: Everyone should participate in cancer screening to detect and treat it early.

ZH: 这个卫生院提供免费的筛检服务，吸引了很多人前来。
EN: This clinic offers free screening services, attracting many people.

ZH: 尿蛋白筛检可以检测肾脏健康情况。
EN: Urine protein screening can detect kidney health.

ZH: 老年人应该定期进行血糖筛检，预防糖尿病。
EN: Elderly individuals should have regular blood sugar screening to prevent diabetes.

ZH: 体检中包括了多项筛检项目，全面了解身体健康情况。
EN: Health examinations include various screening tests to comprehensively understand one's health.

ZH: 筛检是一种积极健康管理的方式，能够预防疾病。
EN: Screening is a proactive health management approach that can prevent diseases.

ZH: 对家族史有疾病的人群，筛检尤为重要。
EN: Screening is especially important for populations with a family history of diseases.

ZH: 肠镜筛检是早期发现结直肠癌的有效手段。
EN: Colonoscopy screening is an effective way to detect colorectal cancer early.

ZH: 此次筛检结果显示肝功能正常。
EN: The screening results indicate normal liver function.

ZH: 这个乡村医疗中心提供了免费的白内障筛检服务。
EN: The rural medical center offers free cataract screening services.

ZH: 获得筛检阳性结果并不意味着一定会得到疾病。
EN: Getting a positive screening result does not necessarily mean one will have the disease.

ZH: 定期筛检是预防疾病的有效措施。
EN: Regular screening is an effective measure to prevent diseases.
